{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzY0OTU3NDQw", "number": 1198, "title": "Feature/submissions and assessments/assessing before due date warning", "bodyText": "Checklist\n\n I tested all changes and all related features with different users (student, tutor, instructor, admin) on the test server https://artemistest.ase.in.tum.de.\n Client: I added multiple integration tests (Jest) related to the features\n Client: I added authorities to all new routes and check the course groups for displaying navigation elements (links, buttons)\n Client: I documented the TypeScript code using JSDoc style.\n Client: I added multiple screenshots/screencasts of my UI changes\n Client: I translated all the newly inserted strings into German and English\n\nDescription\n\nCurrently, instructors have full access rights to all operations of Artemis, including assessing a submission although the due date is not over yet. In some situations, this may lead to students sharing sample solutions with other students before the due date. Therefore we should warn the instructors in the \"submissions and assessments\" page if the due date is not over yet.\nSteps for Testing\n\nMake sure to login as an instructor\n\nNavigate to Overview and click on the exercise detail page of Text|Modeling|FileUpload exercises\nClick on \"submissions\" under instructor actions\nA warning sign should be displayed\nNavigate to Tutor Exercise Dashboard\nA warning sign should be displayed there as well\n\nScreenshots", "createdAt": "2020-01-20T18:27:17Z", "url": "https://github.com/ls1intum/Artemis/pull/1198", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "acd1a9cb63d24eda954fa68d20d061dd80c0976b"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-01-28T08:50:15Z", "author": {"login": "HanyaElhashemy"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 24, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABb8QIAugH2gAyMzY0OTU3NDQwOjAzMDNhMjhkZDJlODJhOTFkMDllNWE4NDg0M2Y2OWZlMmY1NzZhNGQ=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABb-tXkH